abstract: What started off as an odd couple evolved into a friendship unlike any between a president and vice president in modern times.

abstract: The Democratic Party has never nominated a presidential candidate from west of the Central time zone. The former governor of Colorado believes he can change that.
snippet: The Democratic Party has never nominated a presidential candidate from west of the Central time zone. The former governor of Colorado believes he can change that.
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, N.H. — In its 191-year history, the Democratic Party has never nominated a presidential candidate from west of the Central time zone.

abstract: Despite doubts about his candidacy, Joe Biden begins the race with substantial support from three key constituencies in his native state, a place the Democrats can’t afford to lose again.

lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — The case for Joseph R. Biden Jr. has always come down to Pennsylvania.

headline_main: In Pennsylvania, Joe Biden Finds Support Where He Most Needs It
headline_print_headline: Biden’s Appeal Taps the Voters His Party Needs

abstract: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.
snippet: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Barack Obama did not think Joseph R. Biden Jr. should run for president — he hardly needed to say it out loud for aides to understand that. The trick that summer of 2015 was finding a way to nudge Mr. Biden to stay out of the race without looking as if he was nudging Mr. Biden to stay out of the race.

abstract: Mr. Sanders’s campaign kicked off its national organizing program Saturday with what it says are roughly 5,000 events across every state.
snippet: Mr. Sanders’s campaign kicked off its national organizing program Saturday with what it says are roughly 5,000 events across every state.
lead_paragraph: Just days after former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. became the 20th candidate to join the Democratic presidential race, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont readied what he hoped would be his latest show of force: thousands of house parties across the country.
